This introduces the handling of semicolons; however it may truncate a
filename on a quoted semicolon [to be fixed].

axel: Fix speed-limiting sleep delay overflow

This caused Axel to stall when using over 4 connections.

Fix it by using uint64_t, and use a base-2 representation to enable a
trivial division step for the result.

Fixes: https://github.com/axel-download-accelerator/axel/issues/338
Signed-off-by: Ismael Luceno <ismael@iodev.co.uk>

conn: Split redirection loop check code into functions

Also simplify axel_rand64 to tail-call into the read function.

Signed-off-by: Ismael Luceno <ismael@iodev.co.uk>

conn: Improve redirect loop detection with hashing

This reduces the BSS + heap consumption from about 1.1 KB per URL to a
fixed 1 KB buffer plus 4 bytes per URL, which is a 78% reduction for the
default limit, or 76% when taking into account the extra code.
conn: Make conn_url return the URL length
Add function to get random numbers from /dev/random

Add a simple 32-bit hashing function

Based on the reference SipHash-2-4-32 implementation.
conf: Remove redundant string termination in parse_interfaces

conf: Merge output modes into a single field

Phase out "alternate_output" and "percent" in favour of a new
"progress_style" setting. Configuration file is affected but
CLI arguments are unchanged for now.
